And I'm Erika.
我是 Erika。

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:12,960
And today we're going to be talking about one of our favorite topics as always.
今天我们要聊一个我们一直最喜欢的话题。

5
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:13,960
Food.
食物。

6
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:14,960
Food.
食物。

7
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:15,960
We're going to be at a restaurant.
我们要去一家餐厅。

8
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:20,760
And, you know, one of the most difficult or embarrassing things to deal with at a restaurant
你知道，在餐厅里最尴尬或最难处理的事情之一

9
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:25,440
is what to say when you don't like the food or when it's bad quality food.
就是当你不喜欢食物或者食物质量差时该说什么。

10
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:26,440
Right.
没错。

11
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:29,960
So maybe we have to complain about the food or maybe even the service, right?
所以也许我们得抱怨食物，甚至服务，对吧？

12
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:30,960
That's right.
对。

13
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:36,000
And in this lesson, we're going to be learning some really wonderful words and phrases that
在这节课里，我们将学习一些非常棒的单词和短语，

14
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,360
you can use when you need to complain about the food or the service in a restaurant.
当你需要在餐厅抱怨食物或服务时可以使用。

15
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,360
Okay.
好的。

16
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:45,960
So before we listen to what happens in this restaurant with this food, let's take a look
所以在听这家餐厅里关于食物的故事之前，我们先快速看一下

17
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:49,880
very quickly at vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

18
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:50,880
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

19
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:51,880
Okay.
好的。

20
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:54,280
We're only going to do one word today.
今天我们只讲一个词。

21
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:56,640
And this you'll hear in the dialogue.
这个词你会在对话中听到。

22
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,640
An establishment.
一家场所。

23
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,640
Establishment.
场所。

24
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:01,200
This kind of establishment.
这种场所。

25
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,200
Okay.
好的。

26
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:05,560
So when I say an establishment, that's a noun.
所以当我说“场所”时，它是一个名词。

27
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:07,080
What is an establishment?
什么是场所？

28
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:11,360
It's basically a fancy word for a business or a restaurant in this case.
基本上就是“企业”或“餐厅”的正式说法，这里指餐厅。

29
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,360
In this case, it's a restaurant.
这里指的是餐厅。

30
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,360
Yeah.
是的。

31
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:15,140
But in general, you can say it's a business.
但一般来说，你可以说它是一个企业。

32
00:01:15,140 --> 00:01:17,360
So you have a very fine establishment.
所以你有一家很高级的场所。

33
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:18,360
That's right.
没错。

34
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:23,040
So an establishment, a type of business, a place of business, really.
所以场所，一种企业，一个经营场所，真的。

35
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:24,040
Very good.
很好。

36
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,040
All right.
好的。

37
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,840
So now it's time for us to listen to our dialogue.
现在是时候听我们的对话了。

38
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:29,040
We're going to find out what's going on here.
我们要看看这里发生了什么。

39
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:33,840
Apparently, there is a very angry customer and we're going to find out why.
显然，有一个非常生气的顾客，我们要找出原因。

40
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:35,840
Excuse me, waiter.
打扰一下，服务员。

41
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:36,840
Yes, sir.
是的，先生。

42
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:40,840
What can I do for you?
我能为您做什么？

43
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:47,240
I've been sitting here for the past 20 minutes and no one has offered me a glass of water,
我在这里坐了20分钟，没人给我倒杯水，

44
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:50,400
brought any bread to the table, and our appetizers haven't been served yet.
没拿面包上桌，我们的开胃菜也没上。

45
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,480
You know, in this kind of establishment, I'd expect much better service.
你知道，在这种场所，我期待更好的服务。

46
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,480
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

47
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,480
I'll check on your order right away.
我马上去查您的订单。

48
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,480
Relax, honey.
放松点，亲爱的。

49
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:00,880
The place is busy tonight and I've heard the food is amazing.
今晚这里很忙，我听说食物很棒。

50
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:01,880
Anyway.
不管怎样。

51
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:02,880
Here you are, sir.
给您，先生。

52
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:06,240
The foie gras for the lady and a mushroom soup for you.
鹅肝给女士，蘑菇汤给您。

53
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,240
Waiter!
服务员！

54
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:12,120
I ordered a cream of mushroom soup with asparagus.
我点的是芦笋奶油蘑菇汤。

55
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:15,000
The soup is obviously too runny and it's over seasoned.
这汤明显太稀了，而且调味过重。

56
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
It's completely inedible.
完全不能吃。

57
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Okay.
好的。

58
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,280
I do apologize for that.
我对此非常抱歉。

59
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,760
Can I bring you another soup or would you like to order something else?
我给您换一份汤，或者您想点别的吗？

60
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,280
Take this foie gras back as well.
把这个鹅肝也拿回去。

61
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,840
It's rubbery and completely overcooked.
它又硬又老，完全煮过头了。

62
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,440
And look at the portion size.
看看这分量。

63
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:28,960
How can you charge $25 for a sliver of duck liver?
一小片鸭肝怎么能收25美元？

64
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:29,960
Right away, sir.
马上，先生。

65
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,960
Honey, come on.
亲爱的，别这样。

66
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,960
The foie gras was fine.
鹅肝没问题。

67
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:35,440
Why are you making such a big deal?
你为什么这么大惊小怪？

68
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,760
Are you trying to get our meal comped again?
你是不是又想让我们这顿饭免单？

69
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,240
What do you mean?
你什么意思？

70
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:42,280
We're paying for this and I'm shelling out my hard earned bucks.
我们付钱吃饭，我花的是自己辛苦赚的钱。

71
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,680
I expect value for money.
我期望物有所值。

72
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,840
Here you are, sir.
给您，先生。

73
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,240
I hope it is all right now.
希望现在没问题了。

74
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,120
The chef has prepared it especially for you.
厨师特意为您准备的。

75
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,120
Yes, fine.
是的，还行。

76
00:02:50,120 --> 00:03:16,280
Honey, are you all right?
亲爱的，你没事吧？

77
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,080
Well I guess that's one lesson.
嗯，我想这是个教训。

78
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:21,320
Hey, if you're in a restaurant, don't be too rude to the waiter.
嘿，如果你在餐厅，别对服务员太粗鲁。

79
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,640
You never know what's going to happen.
你永远不知道会发生什么。

80
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,280
The waiter and the cook, right?
服务员和厨师，对吧？

81
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:27,840
Yeah, you don't want to offend that kitchen staff.
是的，你不想得罪厨房员工。

82
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,840
All right.
好的。

83
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:35,280
So we'll talk about that a little bit later on but now I think we had some really interesting
我们稍后再谈这个，但现在我觉得我们学到了一些非常有趣的

84
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:41,120
vocabulary of how to describe food that is not well prepared and we can take a look at
描述食物做得不好的词汇，我们可以在“语言要点”中看看。

85
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,080
that now in Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

86
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,400
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

87
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:52,120
All right, so the guy in this dialogue, he ordered a mushroom soup and he complained
好的，对话里的那个人点了一份蘑菇汤，他抱怨说

88
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,240
that the mushroom soup was too runny.
蘑菇汤太稀了。

89
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:56,680
Okay, the soup is too runny.
好的，汤太稀了。

90
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,680
Runny.
稀的。

91
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:01,360
So he wanted a cream of mushroom so it should be a little bit thicker.
所以他点的是奶油蘑菇汤，应该浓稠一点。

92
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,360
Yep.
是的。

93
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:04,200
But in this case, it was runny.
但这里，它很稀。

94
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,480
So when something is runny, it's too liquid.
所以当东西很稀时，就是太液态了。

95
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,480
Too liquid.
太液态了。

96
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,480
And I think we can relate it to a runny nose, right?
我觉得我们可以联想到流鼻涕，对吧？

97
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,480
Exactly.
没错。

98
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:15,360
Okay, so when liquid is coming out of your nose, a runny nose, in this case, the soup
好的，当液体从鼻子里流出来时，就是流鼻涕，这里汤是稀的。

99
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,360
is runny.
汤很稀。

100
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,360
Right.
对。

101
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:21,760
And another thing that he was complaining about, the food was over seasoned.
他抱怨的另一件事是食物调味过重。

102
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,760
Over seasoned.
调味过重。

103
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,320
The food is over seasoned.
食物调味过重。

104
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,720
Okay, so if the food is over seasoned.
好的，如果食物调味过重。

105
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,840
It's too salty.
就是太咸了。

106
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,640
So it's another way of saying it's too salty.
所以这是说太咸的另一种方式。

107
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:34,160
Yeah, it's kind of a fancy cooking term.
是的，这有点像高级烹饪术语。

108
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:38,520
Now can I say if there's too much pepper in the food, can I say it's over seasoned?
那如果食物里胡椒太多，我能说它调味过重吗？

109
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,860
Well, technically no.
嗯，严格来说不行。

110
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:44,760
When a cook says something is over seasoned, he's talking salt only.
当厨师说东西调味过重时，他只指盐。

111
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,760
Only salt.
只指盐。

112
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:51,160
So the cream of mushroom is very runny, it's over seasoned, and he said it's completely
所以奶油蘑菇汤很稀，调味过重，他说它完全

113
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,160
inedible.
不能吃。

114
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,160
Inedible.
不能吃。

115
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,160
It's inedible.
它不能吃。

116
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,160
Inedible.
不能吃。

117
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:58,560
Now, this word edible.
现在，这个词“可食用的”。

118
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,560
You can eat it.
你可以吃它。

119
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,560
You can eat it.
你可以吃它。

120
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:03,020
So we have this prefix inedible.
所以我们有前缀“不可-”。

121
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,080
You cannot eat it.
你不能吃它。

122
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,080
This is not possible.
这不可能。

123
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,080
Yep.
是的。

124
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,040
And it doesn't mean that physically you can't eat it.
这并不意味着你身体上不能吃它。

125
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,840
It just means it's pretty disgusting.
只是说它很恶心。

126
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:10,840
Okay.
好的。

127
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,880
This food is inedible.
这食物不能吃。

128
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:18,240
And then he started to complain about the other dish and he said that it's rubbery.
然后他开始抱怨另一道菜，说它又硬又老。

129
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,920
Rubbery.
又硬又老。

130
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,680
The foie gras was rubbery.
鹅肝又硬又老。

131
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,840
All right.
好的。

132
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:26,520
So I think we noticed the word rubber.
我想我们注意到了“橡胶”这个词。

133
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:31,860
So obviously if a food is rubbery, it's too chewy.
所以显然如果食物又硬又老，就是太有嚼劲了。

134
00:05:31,860 --> 00:05:34,160
It's like chewing on the bottom of your shoe, right?
就像嚼鞋底一样，对吧？

135
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,680
Okay, so it's too hard to chew or to swallow.
好的，所以太难嚼或难以下咽。

136
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,680
Exactly.
没错。

137
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,680
All right.
好的。

138
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:43,320
And apparently the food was rubbery because it's completely overcooked.
显然食物又硬又老是因为完全煮过头了。

139
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,320
Overcooked.
煮过头了。

140
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:45,720
All right.
好的。

141
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,560
We have overcooked.
我们有“煮过头”。

142
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:52,700
So when something is overcooked, I mean it's easy to understand that it's cooked too much.
所以当东西煮过头时，很容易理解是煮得太久了。

143
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:54,720
But it doesn't mean that it's burnt, right?
但这不意味着烧焦了，对吧？

144
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,720
No.
不。

145
00:05:55,720 --> 00:06:00,080
So maybe you've ordered your steak to be rare, but it comes to you well done.
所以也许你点了三分熟的牛排，但上来的却是全熟的。

146
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:02,760
So it's not burnt, but it's cooked too much.
所以没烧焦，但煮得太久了。

147
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:05,200
So also I guess we can say like chicken.
所以我想我们也可以说鸡肉。

148
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,880
Sometimes if you overcook chicken, it comes out too dry.
有时如果你把鸡肉煮过头，它会变得太干。

149
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,880
Yep.
是的。

150
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,880
Right.
对。

151
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:12,680
So to overcook something.
所以是煮过头了。

152
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:19,120
And finally he was complaining about the size of the dish and he said, this is a sliver
最后他抱怨菜的分量，他说这是一小片鸭肝。

153
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,560
of duck liver.
一小片鸭肝。

154
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,560
Okay.
好的。

155
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,560
A sliver.
一小片。

156
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,560
A sliver.
一小片。

157
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,560
All right.
好的。

158
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,040
Now this word sliver is like a slice, right?
现在这个词“一小片”就像一片，对吧？

159
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:30,120
A very small, tiny little slice.
非常小的一小片。

160
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,120
Okay.
好的。

161
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:34,520
So we can say, okay, I just want a sliver of bacon for breakfast.
所以我们可以说，好的，我早餐只想吃一小片培根。

162
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,520
All right.
好的。

163
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:39,440
Let's look at a few more examples of how we can use sliver.
让我们再看几个如何使用“一小片”的例子。

164
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,200
Example one.
例子一。

165
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:44,360
No, John's on a diet.
不，John在节食。

166
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:49,280
He'll just have a sliver of cake and no ice cream.
他只要一小块蛋糕，不要冰淇淋。

167
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,520
Example two.
例子二。

168
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:54,520
I'm really full, but it looks so delicious.
我真的很饱了，但它看起来太好吃了。

169
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,920
Can you just cut me a sliver?
你能只给我切一小块吗？

170
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,140
Example three.
例子三。

171
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:03,240
You call this sliver of beef on my plate a meal?
你管我盘子里这一小片牛肉叫一顿饭？

172
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:06,320
There's almost nothing here.
这里几乎什么都没有。

173
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,960
And those are all the words we had for language takeaway.
这些就是我们在“语言要点”里学到的所有词。

174
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:13,480
Now you have, so we've given you different adjectives of describing food that is not
现在你有了，我们给了你不同的形容词来描述做得不好的食物。

175
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,760
well prepared.
做得不好的食物。

176
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:19,720
So now let's move on to some other phrases that the customer used to complain in Fluency
现在让我们继续看顾客在“流利度构建”中用来抱怨的其他短语。

